The paper discusses the limitations of encoder-decoder GAN architectures in learning meaningful encodings for data, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper deals with image distributions. The paper also discusses the role of the encoder in the GAN setup, which is related to the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the GAN objective, which is related to the field of Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Information Theory (cs.IT).
